.TH smi-include "1" "February 2026" "SMI Toolset" "SMI Include Command"
.SH NAME
smi-include \- print the full path for a given library file
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B smi-include
.I BASE_FILE_NAME
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
The
.B smi-include
command takes a base file name and prints its full path within the SMI library directory.
This is typically used in shell scripts to source SMI library files.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.I BASE_FILE_NAME
The name of the library file to include (e.g. \fBbase.sh\fR).
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Source the base library in a script:
.PP
.B . `smi-include base.sh`
.SH AUTHOR
.PP
Command written by Imre Tabur.
.PP
Documentation written by Junie.
